name: FFX-County-Urban-Wildlife-Dashboard-
description: The Fairfax County Urban Biodiversity Dashboard visualizes urban biodiversity patterns using data from the iNaturalist API. Built with Python, D3.js, and Leaflet.js, it provides real-time data integration and environmental metrics tracking. The dashboard helps track and understand wildlife patterns, habitat health, and biodiversity trends.

name: Credit-Card-Clustering-Analysis
description: This project analyzes credit card customer data using K-Medoids and Hierarchical Clustering. It includes data cleaning, outlier detection, exploratory data analysis, and clustering to segment customers. Visualizations and statistical evaluations assess cluster quality for insights into customer behavior.
